<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n53100j"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53100j">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53100j"> 100(j)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~shipwight~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Livery Companies]</font>: [These were survivals of the civic life of medieval London where, for more than six hundred years they formed the active centre of the trade, social and religious life of the merchants and manufacturers of the City. Each was incorporated by an Ordinanace of the Mayor and Aldermen of the City of London, and this was generally followed by a Royal Charter or Act of Parliament. They were granted specific powers, such as of search and seizure, and a livery or costume to distinguish themselves at important functions. They were many and included the <mark>Shipwrights</mark>, and Skinners &mdash; dealers in felt and pelts; and the Mercers, the primary company, who dealt in cloths and colours. <small> Athelstan Ridgway, ed. <a name="RDOD" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#RDOD"><cite title="source">A Dictionary of Dates</cite></a> (1932) L</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
